responded: The root cause of the double free is that `as_name` is sometimes set to `imported->imp_name` (by assignment and nulling out `as_name`), but in the error path (`goto erret`), `vim_free(as_name)` is always called. If the code path does not null out `as_name` after transferring ownership, it will be freed twice: once by the owner (e.g., in `tuple_free_contents` or similar), and once here.

**Fix:** After assigning `imported->imp_name = as_name;`, set `as_name = NULL;` so that the error handler does not free it again.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/src/vim9script.c
+++ b/src/vim9script.c
@@ -635,6 +635,7 @@
 	    imported->imp_name = as_name;
+	    as_name = NULL;
 	    imported->imp_sid = sid;
 	    if (is_autoload)
 		imported->imp_flags = IMP_FLAGS_AUTOLOAD;
