Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/src/tuple.c\n+++ b/src/tuple.c\n@@ -594,10 +594,20 @@\n failret:\n-    if (evaluate)\n-        tuple_free(tuple);\n-    return FAIL;\n+    if (evaluate && tuple != NULL)\n+    {\n+        tuple_free(tuple);\n+        tuple = NULL;\n+    }\n+    return FAIL;\n     }\n \n done:\n     *arg += 1;\n-    if (evaluate)\n-        rettv_tuple_set(rettv, tuple);\n+    if (evaluate)\n+    {\n+        rettv_tuple_set(rettv, tuple);\n+        tuple = NULL; // Avoid double free if function returns to an error handler\n+    }\n \n     return OK;\n }'}`
responded: The root cause of the double free is as follows:

- When parsing and evaluating a tuple, the function `eval_tuple()` creates a new tuple object and may append items to it. If an error occurs during parsing or appending items, the code jumps to the `failret:` label, where it does `tuple_free(tuple)`.
- However, if the first element (`rettv`) is already a tuple (possibly as a result of a nested tuple expression), it may be double-freed: once as part of cleaning up `rettv` (in `clear_tv(&tv)` or `clear_tv(&rettv)` in error handling), and again as part of the tuple clean-up (since `tuple_free_contents`/`tuple_unref` may recurse into items).

**Safe fix proposal:**

- In `eval_tuple`, after passing ownership of the tuple to the `rettv` (with `rettv_tuple_set(rettv, tuple)` at line 603), set `tuple` to `NULL` so that any later error handling (or exit from the function) does not try to free it again.
- Additionally, in the error path (`failret:`), after freeing the tuple, set the local `tuple` pointer to `NULL` as a defensive measure.

Let's produce the patch for `src/tuple.c` to ensure only one free occurs for any tuple object.

```diff
--- a/src/tuple.c
+++ b/src/tuple.c
@@ -594,10 +594,20 @@
 failret:
-    if (evaluate)
-        tuple_free(tuple);
-    return FAIL;
+    if (evaluate && tuple != NULL)
+    {
+        tuple_free(tuple);
+        tuple = NULL;
+    }
+    return FAIL;
     }

 done:
     *arg += 1;
-    if (evaluate)
-        rettv_tuple_set(rettv, tuple);
+    if (evaluate)
+    {
+        rettv_tuple_set(rettv, tuple);
+        tuple = NULL; // Avoid double free if function returns to an error handler
+    }

     return OK;
 }
```

Now, let's validate this patch.

